-- ECB funding to Italy banks edges lower in November
-- 
-- Fri Dec 7, 2012 5:30am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/12/07/us-italy-banks-ecb-idUSBRE8B60CG20121207

 

 MILAN  (Reuters) - Italian banks held a total of 273 billion euros in funds from the European Central Bank at the end of November, down from 276.5 billion euros ($359 billion) in October, central bank data showed on Friday. 
 Italian lenders took an overall 255 billion euros in three-year funds the ECB lent at two special longer-term tenders in December and February. ($1 = 0.7700 euros) (Reporting by  Antonella Ciancio )